    "body": "Depends on #39724\r\nRelated: #32280, #31621\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\n`:edit <dir>`, `nvim <dir>` relies on `netrw` for browsing local dirs - there's no reason for this to be the case!\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nAdd a builtin Lua directory listing for local `:edit <dir>` and `nvim <dir>`.\r\n\r\nCreate a (very) simple `filetype=directory` buffer to house files. Support opening entries, traversing to parent directory, and refreshing the current directory - nothing more.\r\n\r\n`netrw` remains available for `:Explore`, remote paths, archive browsing, and file operations. Of course, this remains subject to change as this feature progresses.\r\n\r\n## Configurable Knobs\r\n\r\nThis draft keeps the runtime surface small. The following options were chosen\r\nand are subject to change (leave your thoughts!):\r\n\r\n> NOTE: this table was generated by AI and edited by myself.\r\n\r\n| Area | Choice | Rationale |\r\n| --- | --- | --- |\r\n| scope | opens `:e <dir>` ***and*** `nvim <dir>` | `:e <dir>` is the baseline feature and `nvim .` *is* editing a buffer |\r\n| Scope | Local viewing only. | File operations, remote paths, archive browsing, and tree views are out of scope (for now). |\r\n| Filetype | `filetype=directory`. | Recommended by @superatomic, @justinmk, as a canonial surface for this feature. |\r\n| Buffer name | The *absolute* directory path. | Keeps directory buffers addressable through the same path users edited. |\r\n| Buffer marker | `b:nvim_directory` stores the directory path. | Gives the plugin an internal marker without requiring users to inspect buffer text. |\r\n| Buffer type | `buftype=nowrite`. | The listing is a view, not a file to write back. |\r\n| Buffer lifetime | `bufhidden=delete`, unlisted. | Avoids accumulating stale directory listing buffers. |\r\n| Mutability | Rendered `readonly` and non-modifiable. | Prevents accidental edits to generated listing text. |\r\n| Swap/modeline | Swapfile, modeline disabled. | The buffer is generated from filesystem state, not user-authored file contents. |\r\n| Display | One entry per line, names only, directories suffixed with `/`. | Keeps the first version close to a simple file list and avoids a tree/file-manager UI. |\r\n| Parent entry | Shows `../` when the current directory has a parent.\r\n| Sorting | Directories first, then files, sorted by name. | general precedent |\r\n| Escaped display | Control characters and backslashes are escaped for display. | Lets the buffer remain readable while entry actions use stored paths, not displayed text. |\r\n| Parent mapping | `-` opens the parent directory. | general precedent |\r\n| Refresh mapping | `<C-L>` refreshes the current listing. | Reuses the established refresh convention. |\r\n| Highlighting | directories -> `Directory`; ***files have no highlight***. | Keep things simple |\r\n| Error behavior | Scan failures notify at error level and render only safe entries. | A directory buffer can still exist even when its contents cannot be read. |\r\n| `netrw` coexistence | `:Explore` and netrw commands remain available. | Deprecating `netrw` (:pray:) is for later. |",
