            "body": "should we go ahead and introduce a `filetype=directory` ? https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/31621\r\n\r\n> |:edit| on a directory path now opens |nvim-directory|\r\n\r\nthis is a strange phrasing, would suggest maybe `The builtin |nvim-directory| plugin is used to present directory contents in a buffer.`\r\n\r\nAlso generally, we should deemphasize the plugin aspect. Nvim simply \"shows directories\". \r\n\r\n> |netrw| remains available for |:Explore| and remote file operations.\r\n\r\nthis is temporary i assume/hope",
